Now I'm sippin' on gin, thinkin' 'bout nothin', but the pain (pain)

I got enemies at work, coworkers sayin' I'm not sharp enough (sharp enough)
But I know they're just jealous 'cause they ain't never seen my wrath (wrath)
Got a plan, gonna take over, show 'em who I am (who I am)
Get back on top, leave these haters in the pan

Aunt Edna died last week, still missin' her smile (missin')
Left me thinkin' about life and time flyin' by (time flyin')
Never got to make amends, now she's gone for good (gone)
Feelin' guilty like a fool, wish I could turn the clock back (clock back)

Still tryin' to fill this void, that's been here since youth (youth)
Tryna fit in, but I don't belong, just makin' some noise (noise)
People talkin', gossipin', spreadin' lies and rumors (lies and rumors)
Like a ghost in their minds, they can't get rid of my memories (memories)

[Chorus]
Fallin' apart, fallin' down (down)
No way outta this town (town)
Keepin' up appearances, hide what's real (what's real)
Tryna keep my head above water (above water), don't wanna feel

[Verse 2 - 32 bars]
Gotta keep movin', no stoppin' me (no stoppin')
Even when the world outside says "give up" (give up)
Just need one spark to ignite (spark to ignite)
Unleash the beast within me, that's fight or flight

Mama said be strong, she didn't want to lose me (lose me)
Dad was always there, tried to help me make sense (make sense)
But they ain't prepared me for life's battles (life's battles)
Took lessons from them streets, that made me harder than nails (harder than nails)

Money talkin', people walkin' all around me (walkin' all around me)
Don't nobody care about another man's legacy (legacy)
Fake friendships go by quickly (fake friendships go by quick)
But I won't give 'em an inch of myself, gotta protect my niche

In the mirror's reflection, don't recognize this face (face)
Lookin' worn out, lost, outta place (place)
My life is full of holes, empty spaces (empty spaces)
Guess that's why I'm standin' right here, facin' blank pages

[Outro]
It's like I said before (before)
My story ain't done yet (yet)
These demons in my brain (brain)
Will never let me live...

(beat fades out)

Society's expectations, they're weighin' me down suffocatin' under pressure, can't drown out the sound of my heart racin', it's beatin' like a drum my grip on reality's slippin' away, day by day I'm losin' control, driftin' further astray

[Bridge]
In the dark of the night, when nobody's around I let the tears fall, allow myself to be found my facade crumbles, revealin' the real me behind the mask, a shattered soul, broken and blind

[Chorus]
Got demons in my head, whisperin' "you're dead" voices in the darkness, where I lay my bed they're tryin' to drive me crazy, tear me apart I gotta keep on fightin', playin' the devil's part

This is my life story, etched in stone ain't no erasin' it, so I might as well own it, write it in my own blood still tryin' to make sense, tryin' to rise above the noise, tryin' to find my voice in this constant battle, where only one survives.
